<task id="R3-052" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit + migrate `notification-new-events.json`</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Audit decision: MIGRATED.
      4 audit checks: (1) No non-existent entity joins (queries `appointment` only — real system entity). (2) No `currentuser` filter. (3) No inline membership FetchXML. (4) However, FetchXML had ZERO membership filtering — description claimed "where user is a team member" but actual query returned ALL appointments system-wide. This is a missing-filter defect, semantically equivalent to A1 (wrong/missing membership scoping).
      Migration: Added `Lookup My Matters` node (actionType=52, entityType=`sprk_matter`, roles=[owner, assignedAttorney, assignedParalegal], includeRelated=false, outputVariable=myMatters). Updated Query node to filter `regardingobjectid in {{joinIds myMatters.ids}}` and added dependsOn=["Lookup My Matters"]. Updated edges chain: Start → Lookup My Matters → Query New Events → Has New Events? → Create Notification.
      EntityType rationale: appointments link to matters via polymorphic `regardingobjectid` lookup (same pattern as documents' `sprk_matter` direct lookup). Mirrors canonical pattern from notification-new-documents.json (task 050).
      JSON validated: 5 nodes, 4 edges, valid syntax.
    </completion-notes>
    <phase>P6</phase>
    <parallel-group>L (with 050, 051)</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <estimated-effort>1h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>playbook-config,migration,audit</tags>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-events.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <dependencies>041, 042</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Audit notification-new-events.json for similar broken membership patterns; if found, migrate to LookupUserMembership.</prompt>
  <goal>If broken pattern found, migrated. If not, document audit + close.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-1C.3">Audit + migrate if applicable</constraint>
